data.name: description.Text
data.value: s: the length of the shortest link l : the length of the longest link p, q: the length of the other two links To assemble the four-bar mechanism, it is necessary that s+p+q>=l When s+p+q=l, no motion is permitted. For s+l < p+q (Grashof kinematic chain), 1) If s is a link connected to the base link at pivot a0, then the mechanism is a crank rocker. 2) If s is the base link, the mechanism is a drag link. 3) If s is the coupler, the mechanism is a double rocker. For s+l > p+q (non-Grashof kinematic chain), the mechanism is a triple rocker.
